    <item>
      <title>Negroni</title>
      <link>https://sidecar.keithjgrant.com/drinks/negroni/</link>
      <pubDate>Fri, 12 Jan 2018 21:27:58 -0500</pubDate>
      
      <guid>https://sidecar.keithjgrant.com/drinks/negroni/</guid>
      <description>
&lt;div class=&#34;recipe-intro p-summary&#34;&gt;The Negroni is my favorite drink. Itâ€™s quite sweet, but also bitter and complex. I make mine with Tanquery gin and Cocchi di Torino vermouth. It can also be served on the rocks, but I prefer it neat.&lt;/div&gt;


&lt;ul class=&#34;ingredients&#34;&gt;&lt;li class=&#34;p-ingredient&#34;&gt;1 oz London dry gin&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li class=&#34;p-ingredient&#34;&gt;1 oz Campari&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li class=&#34;p-ingredient&#34;&gt;1 oz Sweet vermouth&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;



&lt;div class=&#34;instructions e-instructions&#34;&gt;
  Add all ingredients to a shaker along with plenty of ice. Stir for 20&amp;ndash;30 seconds. Strain into a coupe glass.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Garnish with an orange twist.
&lt;/div&gt;


</description>
